            <title>[LU-13155] &quot;lfs migrate&quot; and &quot;lfs mirror&quot; should fallocate() the target file</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13155</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Once the &lt;tt&gt;fallocate()&lt;/tt&gt; functionality in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/9275&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/9275&lt;/a&gt; &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3606&quot; title=&quot;Implement fallocate() support for ldiskfs Lustre&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3606&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3606&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fallocate: Implement fallocate preallocate operation&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; is landed, it would be useful to have &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs migrate&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; and &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs mirror extend&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; call &lt;tt&gt;fallocate()&lt;/tt&gt; to pre-allocate the output file on the OST in order to get more optimal block allocation.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
